              "text": "**Planning article requirements**\n\nI’m looking at the need for an article around 1500-2200 words and thinking maybe I should verify CSS classes. It seems we could create a new article-based template, and it looks like the existing one only uses an OG image and a placeholder icon. The user mentioned an image, but perhaps it’s not necessary if the template doesn’t require one. It sounds like we might create an article without an image and include necessary integrations like JSON-LD and Twitter card tags."
            },
            {
              "type": "summary_text",
              "text": "**Assessing article requirements**\n\nI see that I need to include dates like \"15. Juni 2026\" and format them in ISO for JSON and the sitemap. The Amazon DE affiliate tag should be set to nova079-20, and I’ll need AdSense placeholders as per the template. I might want to monetize with Amazon links for Palworld toys. I'll also ensure proper internal links to various topics but be careful with relative paths. Additionally, I should probably craft the HTML with a good structure and maintain the word count around 1900 while checking CSS for necessary classes."
            },
            {
