              "text": "**Planning article creation**\n\nI need to create an article and I'll use the write_file function with a long HTML format. It’s important to include all requirements and maybe not use code blocks; just plain text for steps, unless the user wants structure. The article should be in German and about \"Palworld Server mieten oder selbst hosten? Der komplette Hosting-Guide 2026.” I think I might aim for around 1900 words and ensure to include necessary HTML elements like OG and Twitter tags, along with AdSense and Amazon Affiliate links."
            },
            {
              "type": "summary_text",
              "text": "**Considering Palworld server facts**\n\nI need to gather facts about setting up a Palworld dedicated server. The server can run through SteamCMD on either Linux or Windows and uses UDP port 8211 by default. For RCON, the default port seems to be 25575, which I should confirm. Player slots support a maximum of around 32 players since version 1.0, with practical recommendations of 4-20 depending on the configuration. RAM is suggested between 8-16 GB, with higher needs for longer sessions. I'll also consider CPU, disk size, network requirements, mods, and backup needs."
            },
            {
              "type": "summary_text",
              "text": "**Updating server/client compatibility**\n\nI need to consider updates regarding server and client version compatibility. For security, it's crucial to avoid exposing the RCON interface, so I should set up a firewall. Also, I need to handle SFTP/SSH keys carefully and ensure that admin passwords aren't shown in any screenshots. Implementing a whitelist could also enhance security. I'll make sure to gather these points before finalizing the recommendations for server setup."
            }
          ]
