      "name": "skill_view",
      "snippet": "{\"success\": true, \"name\": \"static-sites\", \"description\": \"Class-level umbrella for building, deploying, and operating static websites — multi-page SEO sites, Astro SSG portals, Jekyll multilingual sites, mockups, CMS integration, forms, maps, and portfolio management. Covers the full lifecycle from scaffolding to production deployment on Cloudflare Pages, GitHub Pages, or nginx VPS.\", \"tags\": [], \"related_skills\": [], \"content\": \"---\\nname: static-sites\\ndescription: \\\"Class-level umbrella for building, deploying, and operating static websites — multi-page SEO sites, Astro SSG portals, Jekyll multilingual sites, mockups, CMS integration, forms, maps, and portfolio management. Covers the full lifecycle from scaffolding to production deployment on Cloudflare Pages, GitHub Pages, or nginx VPS.\\\"\\ntriggers:\\n  - building a multi-page static website\\n  - creating a tourism portal, marketing site, or content hub\\n  - deploying to Cloudflare Pages or GitHub Pages\\n  - setting up Astro SSG, Jekyll, or pure HTML static sites\\n  - adding forms, maps, or CMS to a static site\\n  - managing a portfolio or community website\\n  - Creating HTML/CSS mockups and design variants\\n  - multilingual static site architecture (DE/EN/FR/IT/ES/ZH)\\n  - static site performance optimization and SEO\\n  - generating game server landing pages from YAML data\\n  - deploying per-game subdomain sites to GitHub Pages\\n---\\n\\n# Static Sites — Class-Level Umbrella\\n\\nThis skill is the **single entry point** for all static website work. Load it first, then drill into the relevant subsection or reference file.\\n\\n## Sub-Sections at a Glance\\n\\n| Domain | What | Key Reference |\\n|--------|------|---------------|\\n| **Multi-page SEO sites** | Pure HTML/CSS/JS with shared nav, footer, hamburger, cookie consent, JSON-LD | `references/website-building.md` |\\n| **Segmented nav / filter bars** | Reusable pill/tab UIs for categories, FAQ chips, admin filters, and content filters | `references/segmented-nav-patterns.md` |\\n| **Astro 5 SSG portals** | JSON-driven content, Lego sections, auto-build cron, multi-language i18n | `references/astro5-static-portal.md` |\\n| **Jekyll multilingual** | Liquid templates, _data-driven content, GitHub Pages deployment, hreflang | `references/multilingual-pure-html.md` |\\n| **Web mockups** | HTML/CSS design variants, encoding checks, responsive layout, design systems | `references/web-mockups.md` |\\n| **Local generated galleries** | Integrate locally generated image batches into existing static sites with side-by-side original/variant comparisons | `references/local-generated-gallery-integration.md` |\\n| **Editorial visual polish** | Premium/publisher-style cleanup passes for heroes, cards, spacing, and contrast on static sites | `references/editorial-visual-polish.md` |\\n| **Brand-conform websites** | Landing pages from Corporate Design mappes — strict CD adherence, real brand assets, Navy Glass/Pop-Art/design-token integration | `references/brand-conform-websites.md` |\\n| **Multi-language pure HTML** | Subdirectory-based i18n (`/en/`, `/fr/`), hreflang tags, language switcher, translation via subagents, Cloudflare Pages no-build deploy | `references/multilingual-pure-html.md` |\\n| **Static site CMS** | Keystatic + Astro, file-based content (JSON/YAML), agent-friendly editing | `references/static-site-cms.md` |\\n| **Generated asset atlases** | Build-time ingestion of generated image sets/manifests, public asset copying, Astro path resolution, and image-first UI integration (cards, heroes, map markers) | `references/generated-asset-atlas.md` |\\n| **Forms & newsletters** | FormSubmit, Web3Forms, MailerLite, Express webhook proxy, VPS deployment | `references/static-site-forms.md` |\\n| **Greenfield Blog Setup** | Full flow: domain → Hermes Space → GitHub Repo → Cloudflare Zone/Pages → Deployed AdSense/Affiliate blog. Connects Porkbun, Cloudflare, GitHub, and Pages into one repeatable pipeline. | `references/greenfield-blog-setup.md` |\\n| **In",
