      "name": "skill_view",
      "snippet": "{\"success\": true, \"name\": \"static-sites\", \"file\": \"references/pure-html-affiliate-content-factory.md\", \"content\": \"# Pure HTML Affiliate Content Factory\\n\\nUse this when a scheduled/static blog job asks for multiple new SEO articles in a pure HTML repo (no build step), especially Amazon Affiliate + generated hero images.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. Pull and inspect first:\\n   ```bash\\n   git pull origin main\\n   ls artikel/*.html\\n   sed -n '1,220p' index.html\\n   sed -n '1,220p' artikel/<good-reference>.html\\n   ```\\n2. Choose topics that do not duplicate existing article filenames, titles, or card themes. Prefer adjacent long-tail topics (e.g. “Aquarium einfahren/Nitritpeak”, “Kampffisch Haltung”, “CO2 im Aquarium”) over rewording existing categories.\\n3. Dispatch parallel writers with explicit constraints:\\n   - repo path\\n   - topic + target filename\\n   - existing article reference file\\n   - date, author, site URL\\n   - Amazon tag and exact link format (`https://www.amazon.de/s?k=KEYWORD&tag=TAG`; HTML-escape `&` as `&amp;`)\\n   - requirement to generate a hero image and embed it as `<img src=\\\"../images/DATEINAME\\\" alt=\\\"...\\\" class=\\\"hero-image\\\">`\\n   - do **not** edit `index.html` or `sitemap.xml`; parent integrates after all agents return\\n4. If the repo has no `generate_blog_image.py`, create a small deterministic Pillow fallback in the repo root instead of blocking. It should output PNGs under `images/` and print the generated path.\\n5. After all articles return, integrate centrally:\\n   - insert cards at the front of the blog grid\\n   - add sitemap entries\\n   - add/verify CSS for real image cards if existing cards only used SVG placeholders\\n   - verify files and links\\n   - commit and push\\n\\n## Required Article Checks\\n\\nBefore integrating, verify the returned article/image files exist in the **active repo root**, not just in the subagent summary. Parallel writers may run from an automation mirror or sibling checkout even when the prompt includes a repo path. Do not trust the summary alone:\\n\\n```bash\\n# From the repo you will commit/push\\nls -l artikel/<new-1>.html artikel/<new-2>.html artikel/<new-3>.html \\\\\\n      images/<new-1>.png images/<new-2>.png images/<new-3>.png\\n```\\n\\nIf files are missing, locate them by filename and copy them into the active repo before editing `index.html`/`sitemap.xml`:\\n\\n```bash\\nfind /c/HermesPortable/home -maxdepth 6 \\\\\\n  \\\\( -name '<new-1>.html' -o -name '<new-1>.png' \\\\) -print\\n# Example recovery from an automation mirror:\\ncp /c/HermesPortable/home/scripts/blog-automation/<site>/artikel/<new>.html artikel/\\ncp /c/HermesPortable/home/scripts/blog-automation/<site>/images/<new>.png images/\\n```\\n\\nFor each article file verify:\\n\\n```bash\\npython - <<'PY'\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nimport re\\nfiles = ['artikel/example.html']\\nfor f in files:\\n    txt = Path(f).read_text(encoding='utf-8')\\n    m = re.search(r'<img src=\\\"\\\\.\\\\./images/([^\\\"]+)\\\"[^>]*class=\\\"hero-image\\\"', txt)\\n    print(f, 'hero=', m.group(1) if m else None,\\n          'img_exists=', Path('images/' + m.group(1)).exists() if m else False,\\n          'amazon_links=', txt.count('tag='),\\n          'og_image=', 'property=\\\"og:image\\\"' in txt,\\n          'jsonld=', 'BlogPosting' in txt)\\nPY\\n```\\n\\nAlso parse `sitemap.xml` with `xml.etree.ElementTree.parse()` after editing.\\n\\n## Card Image CSS Pitfall\\n\\nMany older pure HTML blog indexes use SVG placeholders inside `.card-image` and only style `.card-image svg`. When inserting generated image thumbnails, add this CSS or the images may render at natural size / distort the card:\\n\\n```css\\n.card-image img {\\n  width: 100%;\\n  height: 100%;\\n  object-fit: cover;\\n  display: block;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Integration Pattern\\n\\n- Use generated images on index cards when available; set `loading=\\\"lazy\\\"`.\\n- Use absolute root paths on homepage cards (`/images/...`, `/artikel/...`) and relative image paths inside articles (`../images/...`).\\n- Put all new cards before older cards to",
      "tid": "call_1dpRHPDZA90qNRiHIm7V0ehZ",
      "assistant_msg_idx": 4,
      "args": {
        "name": "static-sites",
        "file_path": "references/pure-html-affiliate-content-factory.md"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "skill_view",
      "snippet": "{\"success\": true, \"name\": \"static-sites\", \"file\": \"references/website-building.md\", \"content\": \"# Website Building — Multi-Page SEO Static Sites\\n\\n**Absorbed from**: `website-building` skill (archived)\\n\\n## Core Principle: ALWAYS Multi-Page, NEVER One-Pager\\n\\n## SaaS Landing Page Conversion Architecture\\n\\nSection order (tested for conversion):\\n```\\n1. HERO → 2. STATS → 3. HOW IT WORKS → 4. FIRST SESSION → 5. WHAT YOU CAN WRITE\\n→ 6. FEATURES → 7. INLINE CTA → 8. TESTIMONIALS → 9. KDP PUBLISHING\\n→ 10. COMPARISON → 11. TWIN PATH → 12. FAQ → 13. FINAL CTA → 14. MINI STATS\\n```\\n\\n## SaaS Content Hierarchy: Primary vs Secondary Business Models\\n\\n**Rule**: For a SaaS product with a secondary white-label/reseller offering, EVERY primary page MUST lead with the SaaS value proposition. Secondary models belong on separate subpages.\\n\\n- **Frontpage** → Pure SaaS, zero white-label sections\\n- **Affiliates** → Pure \\\"promote our SaaS\\\", white-label gets one-liner at bottom\\n- **White-Label** → Dedicated subpage only\\n\\n## Dense Footer Navigation Pattern\\n\\nWhen footer grows to many links:\\n- Keep brand/about block visually larger than link columns\\n- Compress footer headings and link spacing\\n- Multi-column layout on desktop, single column on mobile\\n- Newsletter block separated with subtle top border\\n\\n## Page Inventory Checklist\\n\\n- [ ] Topbar logo (WebP) — same on all pages\\n- [ ] Navigation links — no `#` placeholders\\n- [ ] Cookie consent banner — ALL pages\\n- [ ] OG tags + Twitter Cards\\n- [ ] JSON-LD structured data\\n- [ ] Hreflang tags for multilingual\\n- [ ] Canonical URL\\n- [ ] Mobile hamburger menu\\n- [ ] Responsive: 1024/900/640px breakpoints\\n- [ ] Internal links checked — no broken 404s\\n\\n## Pitfalls\\n\\n1. Don't put white-label on frontpage — user WILL correct this\\n2. Genre grid must use emoji icons, not images (faster load)\\n3. Twin path must be genuinely contrasting\\n4. FAQ must answer real objections\\n5. Multiple CTAs throughout, not just at bottom\\n6. `scroll-margin-top` on sections with fixed header\\n7. `@media (prefers-contrast: more)` for high-contrast users\\n\", \"file_type\": \".md\"}",
      "tid": "call_Oj441tadBIgs5RM37Ym4YBcJ",
      "assistant_msg_idx": 4,
      "args": {
        "name": "static-sites",
        "file_path": "references/website-building.md"
